spanGrp.span: Me, I'm called Unyangi, daughter of Baheba
Mimi naitwa Unyangi binti wa Baheba
When we were growing up recently
We were taught by our mothers
gelasaday danqoje qonales hay fug heesi
Often we tell riddles that were taught by our elders
Huwa tunasimulia vitendawili tuliofundishwa na watu wazima
If you meet one of them, they tell you a riddle and you respond
ha ng'asheeg heet qay siyagay aa gad ewas manang'
It is something we experienced when we were small
Ni mambo tuliokutana nayo tulipokuwa wadogo
aa dumd hay het asees aa gehetu dumd sisarmanay
And then we would often dance
Na sisi tulipokua huwa ngoma tunazocheza
Often we would dance the gerona
abij gey geroon ab mang'ol manal aa gegur shandal
Here we call it gerona, I don't know if in Mang'ola they call it shandala
'Hapa tunaita Gerona sijui mang''ola wanaita Shandal'
dumd ha het silasay sisarmanay asees ab hiji
It is the song we sang yesterday when we danced here
Ni ngoma tulizoimba jana tulizocheza sisi hapa
We often also dance Asimjeeg dances
Huwa tunacheza pia ngoma ya waasimjeega
Ah, I don't remember what they are called
dumd asimjeeg seen asang' ga sisarmanayi
The dances of the Asimjeeg are many
Ngoma ya waasimjega ni nyingi tulizocheza
ng'asheeg siyagay asang' diya ba asimjeega yeen hay iidu aa mad egachun gidab gend jeed eemojig
The Asimjeeg things we did were many, you can say we don't know many because we are inside of other tribes.
Mambo tunayofanya ni mengi sana ya waasimjeega wewe sema mengi hatuyafahamu kwa sababu tupo ndani ya makabila
I think that is my piece.
danqoj ad gebariiny diy gicha elas
The riddles, we like to solve them a lot.
as qom elas danqoje aa gogwen aset aweed iyeeny
Often we are telling riddles until night time
Huwa tunasimulia vitendawili mpaka usiku wa manane
aa gwasuk elil qamn madgwand hay ar danqoje deebug mad elasa
"Yes let's sleep," now there aren't any riddles anymore, we don't tell them to children
Ndipo tulale, sasa havipo tena vitendawili hatuwasimulii watoto tena
What children will you tell riddles to?
ar dumjeeng ga ba buneed ee
mad qwarany danqoje jaft giqonqo shing'ad aa golab jeed barood
There are no riddles, when it is evening a child leaves the field
Haipo vitendawili mtoto ifikapo jioni anatoka shambani
qamn nyas qabar ng'any ar deebug manng'
Now even young children are farming
Sasa huwa wanalima hata watoto wadogo
aa mad qomus qon gwalab ar homd debuug aa gobura
And they can't anymore, they arrive and they are tired
Na hawawezi tena wanafika na wamechoka
To tell them riddles, it's not possible
That is, often it's not possible
qwayiid jaft gicha aa go gwalil gobura
A child, if they arrive they go to sleep, they are tired
Mtoto anafika na anaenda kulala amechoka
So that tomorrow they can wake up and go to school
